    {
      "id": "b3ca6b76-38f0-439d-b256-f069ad8a07f8",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "\\'Etudier la convergence simple, uniforme, de $f(x) = \\sum_{n=0}^\\infty\n    \\bigl(\\Arctan(x+n) - \\Arctan(n)\\bigr)$.",
        "html": "<p>Étudier la convergence simple, uniforme, de <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f(x) = \\sum_{n=0}^\\infty\n    \\bigl(\\Arctan(x+n) - \\Arctan(n)\\bigr)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "91f0e09d-88ee-44f6-9c4a-196b5ee6eec8",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que $f$ est de classe $\\mathcal{C}^1$ sur $\\R$.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f\\)</span> est de classe <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\mathcal{C}^1\\)</span> sur <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\R\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "a29a0bdb-dab2-461b-9a32-e7a28d8bdf20",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Chercher une relation simple entre $f(x)$ et $f(x+1)$.",
        "html": "<p>Chercher une relation simple entre <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f(x)\\)</span> et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f(x+1)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "a0bcd58a-4358-4230-b430-47f5cf749cba",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Trouver $\\lim_{x\\to+\\infty} f(x)$.",
        "html": "<p>Trouver <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\lim_{x\\to+\\infty} f(x)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "ec61cc88-f008-45cb-8431-df335f93854d",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "CVU sur tout $[a,b]$.\n$f(x+1) = f(x) + \\frac\\pi2 - \\Arctan x$.\n$f(x+1) - f(x) \\sim \\frac 1x$ donc la suite $(f(n))$ diverge et\n    $f$ est croissante $ \\Rightarrow  \\lim = +\\infty$.",
        "html": "<p>CVU sur tout <span class=\"math inline\">\\([a,b]\\)</span>. <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f(x+1) = f(x) + \\frac\\pi2 - \\Arctan x\\)</span>. <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f(x+1) - f(x) \\sim \\frac 1x\\)</span> donc la suite <span class=\"math inline\">\\((f(n))\\)</span> diverge et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f\\)</span> est croissante <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Rightarrow  \\lim = +\\infty\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    }
  ]
